# Microservice for Waitlist Operations
1. Be modular
2. Grounding: Read the code for correct information, before making any changes or adding be sure to read and be sure we do not already have it 
3. focus on reusability over everything

# This FastAPI-based microservice manages waitlist operations using a PostgreSQL database.
# It runs in a Docker container and interacts with a separate PostgreSQL container.

# Client Input:
# - email
# - name
# - comment
# - referral_source
# - IP address (automatically captured)

# Features:
# - CRUD operations for waitlist entries
# - Reports new sign-ups to a Telegram bot
# - Runs on port 3030 ONLY

# Tech Stack:
# - FastAPI
# - PostgreSQL
# - Docker
# - Telegram Bot API
